result.name: Sun Kwai Heung BBQ food

reviews.text:
A little more expensive when compared to other Chinese BBQ places that are located within a local residential community, but the quality of the meats are above average. 
It is recommended to eat-in as that will give you the best experience of what it feels like to live as a local in a traditional Southern Chinese community. 
My regular order, is poached chicken and crispy skin BBQ pork, with a salted egg side order. During regular, lunch & dinner times, there may be a bowl of tradition soup offered.

For those who rated 1-3 stars, unlucky as this is one of the best BBQ PORK in HK. Yes it is more expensive (double the price of the others) but it is fresh pork, not frozen!! That alone is worth it. If you are a huge foodie or in the industry like myself, like it is worth every single dollar. Don’t bring your best client there as it isn’t too clean lol

Local hole in the wall bbq restaurant that is famous amongst not only the local community but as well as the rest of the city. Famous for their pork specialties like Chasiu, Crispy Pork Belly and Suckling Pig.
There isn't much places to sit so expect a wait, take out is the option most people would opt for. 

A good thing to note is the times the Cha Siu freshly gets taken out out. 9am, 12pm 330 and 530. So make sure you come around those times and request for the better pieces. Lunch therr is very popular so the good cuts sells out quickly, so go early.
Best cha siu. Hands down
Good taste of suckling pig Rice AKA. Yue Jue Fan

reviews.text: 叉燒好好味😋😋😋😋
同以前唔同咗 燒臘師傅唔係舊時嗰個 啲嘢食冇以前咁好食啦 冇理由浸隻白切雞都會浸爛嘅
叉燒非常好味，燒肉仲係滴緊油嘅！

柴灣名物
我一年買不到五次燒臘, 買的都是#叉燒 , 每次都是#新桂香 。用新鮮豬肉來做叉燒, 口感就是不一樣, 剛買回家的時候,外面的焦糖還是脆脆的。隔天把剩下的放進烤箱微微烤熱, 用來做個快捷的#滑蛋叉燒飯, 一吃難忘 。
